\frac{\sin (2x)}{2x} + \frac{\tan (2x)}{2x} = \frac{\sin (2x)}{2x}\left(1 + \frac{1}{\cos(2x)}\right) < 1 + \frac{1}{\cos (2x)},
x \searrow 0
n \leqslant 4
\begin{align} \frac{\sin (2x)}{2x} + \frac{\tan (2x)}{2x} &= \frac{\tan (2x)}{2x}\left(\cos (2x) + 1\right)\\ &= \frac{\tan (2x)}{2x}2\cos^2 x\\ &= \frac{\cos^2 x}{x}\cdot \frac{2\tan x}{1 - \tan^2 x}\\ &= 2\frac{\cos^2 x}{1-\tan^2 x}\cdot \frac{\tan x}{x}\\ &> 2 \frac{\cos^2 x}{1 - \tan^2 x}. \end{align}
